						               													<description>Colonial Space Wars (CSW) is a tactical game based on a futuristic universe of science fiction that recreates battles between two or more armies. Each army is composed of square game pieces measuring 1.2 x 1.2 inches which represent their units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, pieces move across a rectangular board divided into squares arranged in rows and columns. In a game of CSW, each player has a number of units in his army which is set depending on the faction they are playing.  We call this set of units a &amp;ldquo;Combat Sword. Two basic Combat Swords (Union of Terra and Alpha Centauri Brotherhood) are available for an introductory game of CSW.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game pieces represent the units, troops, and vehicles of a fighting force. The pieces have two sides, Front (Illustration and Health arrow) and Back (Name, Attributes and Skills). A player has some pieces with the skill Leader (X). While these pieces are on the board, they grant X command points at the beginning of each turn. Each side alternates turns, making one or more moves depending on the number of Command points available.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each unit requires a number of command points to be used that turn; this is referred to as &amp;ldquo;Activating &amp;rdquo; the unit. When all command points are spent, the opponent&amp;rsquo;s turn begins. Each unit, upon being activated, can move and act in any order. The possible actions are &amp;ldquo;Move&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Embark/disembark&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Attack&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Use active skills&amp;rdquo;. A typical game is a Sudden Death match, where the winner is the player that eliminates the ir opponent&amp;rsquo;s ability to activate units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
